National Park Service 

4h  ·
Kids of all ages are invited to national parks on April 19th, the first day of #NationalParkWeek, for National Junior Ranger Day!
The Junior Ranger program is a great way to get to know your national parks. In addition to Junior Ranger programs specific to their site, many parks also offer National Theme Junior Ranger Programs. These booklets help kids connect to topics that are important to many places across the National Park Service.
Learn more at: https://www.nps.gov…
